
 File: `man_1_simple_shell`

```man
.TH HSH 18 "December 2025" "Holberton School" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh is a simple UNIX command interpreter written in C.
It executes commands entered by the user or read from standard input.

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.IP
./hsh

Non-interactive mode:
.IP
echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell uses the PATH environment variable to locate executable files.

.SH AUTHOR
James and Maxime by Holberton School students.
